  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Pat the <strong>baby gammon</strong> dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Heat a dry pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>gammon</strong> and cook all over until browned (seared) for approx. 5 min&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: use tongs for greater turning control&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Transfer the <strong>browned&nbsp;gammon</strong> to a baking tray (use <strong>tin foil</strong> to avoid mess!) keeping the pan for later</p>\r\n<p>Season with plenty of <strong>pepper</strong> and place in the oven for 35-40 min or until cooked through and piping hot</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into bite-size pieces</p>\r\n<p>Peel and cut the<strong> parsnip<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and <strong>carrot<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;into bite-size pieces&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>potatoes</strong>, <strong>parsnips</strong> and <strong>carrot</strong> to a separate baking tray, drizzle them with&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place the tray in the oven for an initial 25 min or until everything's starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>diced apricots</strong> up so they are finely chopped&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger&nbsp;</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the<strong> chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>ginger</strong> and <strong>chopped&nbsp;</strong><strong>apricots </strong>and cook for 2-3 min</p>\r\n<p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]&nbsp;</span><strong>water</strong> and the <strong>honey</strong>&nbsp;then reduce the heat to very low and cook for a further 10-15 min or until you have a jammy, coarse<strong> chutney</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: mash the chutney with a fork to bind it together more</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, separate the <strong>sage leaves</strong> from their stems and finely chop</p>\r\n<p>Trim the tails off the <strong>Brussels&nbsp;sprouts</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Tip: cut&nbsp;any larger sprouts in half so that they cook evenly</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/461_step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sage</strong> and <strong>Brussels&nbsp;sprouts</strong>&nbsp;to the baking tray</p>\r\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for a further 10-15 min or until everything is cooked through - this is your <strong>roast veg</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
